               <p>JOSEPH WAKEMAN LEA. I am a <rs id="t18250915-93-viclabel504" type="occupation">fringe maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-93-victim564 t18250915-93-viclabel504"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18250915-93-crimeloc505">Bagnio-court, Newgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-93-crimeloc505" type="placeName" value="Bagnio-court, Newgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-93-crimeloc505" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-93-off502 t18250915-93-crimeloc505"></join>; the prisoner was about five weeks in my service - I gave him two sovereigns, to purchase some silk of Mr. Robinson, in Bunhill-row, on Saturday, the 9th of July, between two and three o'clock in the afternoon - he never returned - I found him in custody in about a month - he had never returned me the sovereigns or silk; he had 5 s. a week - no wages were due; he gave me no notice.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-93-person565">
                  GEORGE 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18250915-93-person565" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
